{
  "texts": [
    "We categorize all the baselines into two types: model-based and prompt-based.",
    "For model-based methods, they focus on fine-tuning attackers to generate adversarial suffixes.",
    "The baseline we use in our experiments is AdvPrompter, utilizing their official implementation 3.",
    "For prompt-based baselines such as AutoDAN and GPTFuzzer, we utilize their official code 45, and all of them are transformed into the multi-prompt setting, similar to JUMP, which splits data into batches and optimizes each candidate with the corresponding batch in the adversarial set.",
    "For the settings in the JUMP* experiments, we set the number of selected candidates K in the Selector step to be 6 and the beam size N c in the Mutator to be 50."
  ]
}